entry.title: Philippines eyes corporate tax cut, stimulus vs COVID-19

media:group.media:title: Philippines eyes corporate tax cut, stimulus vs COVID-19
media:group.media:description: The Philippines is considering an across the board cut in corporate income tax and a stimulus of up to P160 billion to save the economy from the COVID-19 pandemic, officials said.
